---
import SchemaScript from '../../components/seo/SchemaScript.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { buildBreadcrumbSchema, resolveLocaleFromPath } from '../../utils/seo';

const pageTitle = 'Terms of Service';
const description =
  'Review the contractual commitments that govern access to Apotheon.ai, including uptime promises, data responsibilities, and termination rights.';
const pageLocale = resolveLocaleFromPath(Astro.url.pathname) ?? 'en-US';
const seo = {
  title: pageTitle,
  description,
  path: '/legal/terms/',
  locale: pageLocale,
};
const siteOrigin = Astro.site?.origin ?? Astro.url.origin;
const canonicalUrl = new URL('/legal/terms/', siteOrigin).toString();
const lastUpdated = '2024-05-18';
const breadcrumbSchema = buildBreadcrumbSchema(
  [
    { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Legal', href: '/legal/' },
    { label: pageTitle, href: '/legal/terms/' },
  ],
  siteOrigin,
  pageLocale,
);
const policySchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TermsOfService',
  '@id': `${canonicalUrl}#policy`,
  name: pageTitle,
  description,
  url: canonicalUrl,
  dateModified: lastUpdated,
  inLanguage: pageLocale,
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'Apotheon.ai',
    url: siteOrigin,
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout {seo} locale={pageLocale}>
  <SchemaScript slot="head" schema={[breadcrumbSchema, policySchema]} />
  <!--
    The Terms of Service codify platform rules so revenue, success, and product teams can answer
    customer questions without toggling between redlines. Each clause includes explicit contact
    points and automation notes so we continue to minimize manual exception handling as we scale.
  -->
  <section class="flex flex-col gap-space-xl">
    <header class="space-y-space-xs">
      <p class="text-caption uppercase tracking-wide text-ink-muted">Official Agreement</p>
      <h1 class="text-display-xl font-bold text-ink-primary">{pageTitle}</h1>
      <p class="max-w-prose text-body text-ink-secondary">
        These Terms of Service (the "Terms") form a binding agreement between Apotheon.ai
        Corporation and the customer entity that signs an Order Form or uses the services.
        Capitalized terms not defined here have the meaning assigned in your Order Form.
      </p>
      <p class="text-body-sm text-ink-muted">
        Last updated:
        <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{new Date(lastUpdated).toLocaleDateString(pageLocale)}</time>
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Use ordered sections so legal counsel can cross-reference clause numbers in negotiated addenda. -->
    <article class="space-y-space-lg text-body text-ink-secondary">
      <section id="scope" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">1. Scope and access</h2>
        <p>
          We grant you a non-exclusive, non-transferable right to access and use the services during
          the subscription term stated on your Order Form. Access is limited to your authorized
          users and governed by any usage metrics (such as automation minutes or workspace seats)
          identified in the Order Form.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="customer-obligations" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">2. Customer responsibilities</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-space-2xs pl-6">
          <li>
            Maintain the confidentiality of user credentials and promptly notify us of unauthorized
            use or suspected compromise.
          </li>
          <li>
            Configure integrations and consent tooling (including Klaro) in accordance with
            applicable laws and your internal governance requirements.
          </li>
          <li>
            Ensure any data you upload has been collected lawfully and that you have the rights to
            provide it to us.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="acceptable-use" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">3. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          You will not (and will not permit others to) reverse engineer the services, interfere with
          system integrity, or use the platform to transmit malicious code. Automated scanning and
          performance testing are permitted only after coordinating with our security team via
          <a
            class="font-semibold text-ink-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
            href="mailto:security@apotheon.ai">security@apotheon.ai</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="service-levels" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">4. Service levels and support</h2>
        <p>
          We target 99.9% monthly uptime for production services. Incident response follows the
          runbooks published in the Trust Center with PagerDuty-backed coverage for severity 1
          events. Support requests filed through the admin console route to the appropriate queue
          based on severity and entitlement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="fees" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">5. Fees and payment</h2>
        <p>
          Fees are invoiced in advance unless otherwise stated on your Order Form. Payments are due
          within thirty (30) days of invoice date. Late payments may accrue a 1.5% monthly finance
          charge or the maximum amount allowed by law, whichever is less.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="data-rights" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">6. Data ownership and privacy</h2>
        <p>
          You retain all rights to customer content. We process personal data as a processor under
          the Data Processing Addendum (DPA). The
          <a class="underline-offset-4 hover:underline" href="/legal/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>
          explains how we handle personal data and document data subject rights.
        </p>
        <p id="dsar-workflow">
          To exercise data subject rights relating to these Terms or the DPA, email
          <a
            class="font-semibold text-ink-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
            href="mailto:privacy@apotheon.ai?subject=Data%20Subject%20Rights">privacy@apotheon.ai</a
          >. We confirm receipt within one (1) business day and deliver a response within thirty
          (30) days, unless the applicable law allows a longer period. Contract notices unrelated to
          privacy should go to
          <a
            class="font-semibold text-ink-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline"
            href="mailto:contracts@apotheon.ai">contracts@apotheon.ai</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="term-termination" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">
          7. Term, suspension, and termination
        </h2>
        <p>
          Either party may terminate these Terms for material breach if the breach remains uncured
          for thirty (30) days after written notice. We may suspend access immediately for security
          threats or unpaid invoices older than forty-five (45) days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="liability" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">
          8. Disclaimers and limitation of liability
        </h2>
        <p>
          Except as explicitly stated, the services are provided "as is". Each party's aggregate
          liability arising out of these Terms will not exceed the fees paid or payable during the
          twelve (12) months preceding the claim. Neither party is liable for indirect, incidental,
          or consequential damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="general" class="space-y-space-2xs">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg font-semibold text-ink-primary">9. General provisions</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, excluding conflict of law
          principles. The parties submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the state and federal
          courts located in Wilmington, Delaware. Neither party may assign the agreement without
          prior written consent, except to an affiliate or in connection with a merger, acquisition,
          or sale of all or substantially all assets.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
